{
  "texts": [
    "By seamlessly integrating adaptive learning elements (Alam, 2022; Rane et al., 2023; Shih et al., 2021), AI systems are designed to further enhance the efficacy of personalized instruction.",
    "Adaptive learning algorithms dynamically adjust instructional content and strategies based on individual learner progress and performance (Kabudi et al., 2021; Lee et al., 2022; Lo, 2023).",
    "To educators, instructional designers, AI researchers, and developers, this fusion of AI-driven personalization and adaptive learning holds the promise of augmenting the transformative potential of educational technologies in enhancing the learning experiences (Chang et al., 2023).",
    "According to Pardos and Bhandari (2023) and Saetra (2022), recent bots powered by generative AI technologies can leverage their knowledge from Language Model (LLM) training to enhance their effectiveness compared to human tutors.",
    "However, there are still challenges and implications of LLM that herald to understanding how and to what extent these technologies can reshape space of possibilities for PL (Grassini, 2023; Whalen & Mouza, 2023)."
  ]
}